00:32:15.979 --> 00:32:21.609
One trick that I find useful when trying to
optimize my white space is to take a screenshot

00:32:21.609 --> 00:32:24.769
of my app as is and start shrinking it down
gradually.

00:32:24.769 --> 00:32:31.039
Shrink it down to about 25%, to even 10% of
its original size and look at that.

00:32:31.039 --> 00:32:36.989
If you can still pick out your white space
from the text, and if it doesn't look even,

00:32:36.989 --> 00:32:42.890
if it doesn't seem like there's a natural
balance in the negative space and the actual

00:32:42.890 --> 00:32:46.989
text and content, then you probably have a
white space problem.

00:32:46.989 --> 00:32:51.639
